My guild *im just an officer mind ya now* is fairly small it consists of friends and that alone keeps it together. Although we might wish to do more active raids the raids are not what keep us together more than the social and psychological atmosphere that comes from knowing your among safe friends. I would think that maybe a better infrastructure that puts certain cliques with their own leader type to keep that leader satisfied and then that leader will have their own followers that stay around for the same friendship reasons might be a good tactic. I am unsure how you dole out your leaders though. It would be a personal choice thing for you. You have a very big base of users but big isnt necessarily always a good thing. You might have beuracracy over who gets to do what going on that will cause splits as some leave because so and so is a snot or so and so didnt let me loot that item or so and so can do this but Im told im not allowed etc etc.. about anything you can picture siblings in a family fighting over is what you could find among members. The more members the higher chance of sibling rivalry so to speak and power hungry toons competiting. What power is there of a lead? Not much if they have no followers be my guess.. but they still want a title *shrug* No clue if any of this helps.. I wish you luck in your keeping a guild alive.

