I am a new member in The Nine Chambers guild. First off, these are MATURE, kind, helpful people. The guild chatter is non stop. I think these factors keep things very alive.

I just attended my first Guild event which was a language class. People who knew a language created a hot keyed phrase in an unknown tongue and clicked it over and over for the assembled group. They did this as long as someone needed to attain mastery. It was wild.

We would run back and forth across the zone to check our results. At one point I was learning Elder Dragon, Thieves chant and something else all simultaneously. I highly recommend this as a group event. People didn't want to go to bed because it was so fun. Some were still up at 3AM EST.

